# SPDX-Licence-Identifier: EUPL-1.2
#
# Use Gemma 4 from your IDE — JetBrains HTTP Client requests for a local
# lem serve (go-inference). Open this file in IntelliJ/GoLand/PyCharm (or run
# with the `ijhttp` CLI) and click the ▶ beside each request.
#
# The `jetbrains-http-client` generator can emit a full .http suite from the
# OpenAPI spec (task sdk with a config naming that generator); this file is
# the curated tour: models, a two-turn conversation, the thinking toggle.

### List the served models
GET {{base}}/v1/models

### Chat — thinking OFF for a crisp answer
POST {{base}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gemma4",
  "max_tokens": 192,
  "chat_template_kwargs": {"enable_thinking": false},
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "My favourite colour is teal. Reply with one short sentence."}
  ]
}

### Chat turn 2 — resend the history; the model recalls the fact
POST {{base}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gemma4",
  "max_tokens": 192,
  "chat_template_kwargs": {"enable_thinking": false},
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "My favourite colour is teal. Reply with one short sentence."},
    {"role": "assistant", "content": "Teal is a beautiful and vibrant colour."},
    {"role": "user", "content": "What is my favourite colour? Answer with just the colour."}
  ]
}

### Chat — thinking ON (the gemma4 default): the reasoning arrives as a
### separate `thought` field, the answer stays clean
POST {{base}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gemma4",
  "max_tokens": 512,
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "Is 17 prime? One word."}
  ]
}

### Anthropic-style route, same serve
POST {{base}}/v1/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gemma4",
  "max_tokens": 192,
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "Say hello in exactly two words."}
  ]
}
